Getting Started with Noteable

What and why of Noteable

Noteable is a service which provides hosted access to Jupyter notebooks - it is maintained by EDINA and the universitys Information Services. Access is provided free to all UoE staff and students.

Noteable is equivalent to running a Jupyter notebook on your local machine, except that all of the configuration and systems administration has been taken care of (e.g.all of the necessary Python packages are already installed). Additionally, as it is entirely web based you will be able to connect from any device with a web browser.

For some useful introductory materials please see the documentation here.

Logging in

As a UoE student you should already have access to Noteable and can login using your university creditials via ease. You can connect to the service via the link provided on Learn or going to noteable.edina.ac.uk/login directly.

Once logged in make sure to start a Standard Notebook (Python 3) instance, and you should be ready to go.

If your previous server is still running you will be asked to either Reconnect or Shut Down - either option is fine, but generally the former is faster if everything was working correctly.

Getting Workshop materials

Each week we will be providing a link for Noteable users which will link to a GitHub repository containing all of that weeks materials. To bring these materials into Noteable you will need to click the +GitRepo button in the upper right.

This will present a modal dialog where the repo link can be entered, once this is done clicking clone will create a local copy of the repository for you within Noteable.

Downloading files

After completing each worksheet you need to render your notebook to PDF. This PDF will then be turned into via Gradescope, before the deadline, in order to receive credit for that assignment. The rendering process will be detailed in the worksheets, but the resulting PDF (or any other file) can be downloaded by selecting the file via the checkboxes on the lefthand side, and then clicking download.
